Package binarytree

Class Node

java.lang.Object
binarytree.Node
All Implemented Interfaces:
binarytree.INode
public class Node extends Object implements binarytree.INode
Node class that has an ID, and a left, right, and parent node. Uses recursion to search the binary tree that it creates to display the tree, and find other nodes within the tree. This class is a good review of recursion.
Author:
jackrutherford

  • Method Details

    • addChild

      public boolean addChild​(String ID, String parentID)
      This method checks to see if a node with the parentID exists in the tree. If not, it returns false after printing an appropriate message. If the node exists, the method checks to see if it already has two children. If it does, the method returns false. Otherwise, it either adds the new node as the parent node’s left child (if the parent has no children) or as the right child (if the parent already has one child). A recursive approach is used.
      Specified by:
      addChild in interface binarytree.INode
      Parameters:
      ID - The ID of the new node to be added to the tree.
      parentID - The ID of the parent of the new node.
      Returns:
      true if new node was added successfully, false otherwise.

    • find

      public binarytree.INode find​(String value)
      This method looks within the tree to find if “value” (the ID of the node to be found) is contained in that subtree. As the search progresses down the tree different nodes will be calling find().
      Specified by:
      find in interface binarytree.INode
      Parameters:
      value - a string (ID of a node) to be found in the tree
      Returns:
      the node, if found; null otherwise.
